{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This may sound strange,"},{"time":2000,"text":"but I'm a big fan of the concrete block."},{"time":4000,"text":"The first concrete blocks were manufactured in 1868"},{"time":7000,"text":"with a very simple idea:"},{"time":9000,"text":"modules made of cement of a fixed measurement"},{"time":12000,"text":"that fit together."},{"time":14000,"text":"Very quickly concrete blocks became"},{"time":16000,"text":"the most-used construction unit in the world."},{"time":19000,"text":"They enabled us to to build things that were larger than us,"},{"time":21000,"text":"buildings, bridges,"},{"time":23000,"text":"one brick at a time."},{"time":25000,"text":"Essentially concrete blocks had become"},{"time":27000,"text":"the building block of our time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"Almost a hundred years later in 1947,"},{"time":32000,"text":"LEGO came up with this."},{"time":34000,"text":"It was called the Automatic Binding Brick."},{"time":37000,"text":"And in a few short years,"},{"time":39000,"text":"LEGO bricks took place in every household."},{"time":42000,"text":"It's estimated that over 400 billion bricks have been produced --"},{"time":45000,"text":"or 75 bricks for every person on the planet."},{"time":48000,"text":"You don't have to be an engineer"},{"time":50000,"text":"to make beautiful houses, beautiful bridges, beautiful buildings."},{"time":53000,"text":"LEGO made it accessible."},{"time":55000,"text":"LEGO has essentially taken the concrete block, the building block of the world,"},{"time":58000,"text":"and made it into the building block"},{"time":60000,"text":"of our imagination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"Meanwhile the exact same year,"},{"time":64000,"text":"at Bell Labs the next revolution was about to be announced,"},{"time":67000,"text":"the next building block."},{"time":69000,"text":"The transistor was a small plastic unit"},{"time":71000,"text":"that would take us from a world"},{"time":73000,"text":"of static bricks piled on top of each other"},{"time":75000,"text":"to a world where everything was interactive."},{"time":77000,"text":"Like the concrete block,"},{"time":79000,"text":"the transistor allows you to build"},{"time":81000,"text":"much larger, more complex circuits, one brick at a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"But there's a main difference:"},{"time":86000,"text":"The transistor was only for experts."},{"time":88000,"text":"I personally don't accept this,"},{"time":90000,"text":"that the building block of our time"},{"time":92000,"text":"is reserved for experts,"},{"time":94000,"text":"so I decided to change that."},{"time":97000,"text":"Eight years ago when I was at the Media Lab,"},{"time":99000,"text":"I started exploring this idea"},{"time":101000,"text":"of how to put the power of engineers"},{"time":103000,"text":"in the hands of artists and designers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"A few years ago I started developing littleBits."},{"time":108000,"text":"Let me show you how they work."},{"time":112000,"text":"LittleBits are electronic modules"},{"time":115000,"text":"with each one specific function."},{"time":118000,"text":"They're pre-engineered"},{"time":120000,"text":"to be light, sound,"},{"time":123000,"text":"motors and sensors."},{"time":125000,"text":"And the best part about it"},{"time":127000,"text":"is they snap together with magnets."},{"time":130000,"text":"So you can't put them the wrong way."},{"time":133000,"text":"The bricks are color-coded."},{"time":135000,"text":"Green is output, blue is power,"},{"time":138000,"text":"pink is input and orange is wire."},{"time":140000,"text":"So all you need to do is snap a blue to a green"},{"time":143000,"text":"and very quickly you can start making larger circuits."},{"time":146000,"text":"You put a blue to a green,"},{"time":148000,"text":"you can make light."},{"time":150000,"text":"You can put a knob in between"},{"time":154000,"text":"and now you've made a little dimmer."},{"time":157000,"text":"Switch out the knob"},{"time":160000,"text":"for a pulse module,"},{"time":162000,"text":"which is here,"},{"time":165000,"text":"and now you've made a little blinker."},{"time":169000,"text":"Add this buzzer"},{"time":171000,"text":"for some extra punch"},{"time":173000,"text":"and you've created a noise machine."},{"time":175000,"text":"I'm going to stop that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"So beyond simple play,"},{"time":180000,"text":"littleBits are actually pretty powerful."},{"time":182000,"text":"Instead of having to program, to wire, to solder,"},{"time":185000,"text":"littleBits allow you to program"},{"time":187000,"text":"using very simple intuitive gestures."},{"time":189000,"text":"So to make this blink faster or slower,"},{"time":191000,"text":"you would just turn this knob"},{"time":193000,"text":"and basically make it pulse faster or slower."},{"time":196000,"text":"The idea behind littleBits"},{"time":198000,"text":"is that it's a growing library."},{"time":200000,"text":"We want to make every single interaction in the world"},{"time":202000,"text":"into a ready-to-use brick."},{"time":204000,"text":"Lights, sounds, solar panels, motors --"},{"time":206000,"text":"everything should be accessible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208000,"text":"We've been giving littleBits to kids and seeing them play with them."},{"time":211000,"text":"And it's been an incredible experience."},{"time":213000,"text":"The nicest thing is how they start to understand"},{"time":215000,"text":"the electronics around them from everyday"},{"time":217000,"text":"that they don't learn at schools."},{"time":219000,"text":"For example, how a nightlight works,"},{"time":221000,"text":"or why an elevator door stays open,"},{"time":223000,"text":"or how an iPod responds to touch."},{"time":226000,"text":"We've also been taking littleBits to design schools."},{"time":228000,"text":"So for example, we've had designers"},{"time":231000,"text":"with no experience with electronics whatsoever"},{"time":233000,"text":"start to play with littleBits as a material."},{"time":236000,"text":"Here you see, with felt and paper water bottles,"},{"time":239000,"text":"we have Geordie making ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"(Clanging)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"(Buzzing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":245000,"text":"A few weeks ago we took littleBits to RISD"},{"time":248000,"text":"and gave them to some designers"},{"time":250000,"text":"with no experience in engineering whatsoever --"},{"time":252000,"text":"just cardboard, wood and paper -- and told them \"Make something.\""},{"time":255000,"text":"Here's an example of a project they made,"},{"time":257000,"text":"a motion-activated confetti canon ball."},{"time":260000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":262000,"text":"But wait, this is actually my favorite project."},{"time":266000,"text":"It's a lobster made of playdough"},{"time":271000,"text":"that's afraid of the dark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"To these non-engineers, littleBits became another material,"},{"time":280000,"text":"electronics became just another material."},{"time":282000,"text":"And we want to make this material accessible to everyone."},{"time":285000,"text":"So littleBits is open-source."},{"time":287000,"text":"You can go on the website, download all the design files, make them yourself."},{"time":290000,"text":"We want to encourage a world"},{"time":292000,"text":"of creators, of inventors, of contributors,"},{"time":295000,"text":"because this world that we live in,"},{"time":297000,"text":"this interactive world, is ours."},{"time":299000,"text":"So go ahead and start inventing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}